---------------------------------\n    54→// Shared entity tables (used by both legacy single-db and per-tenant dbs)\n    55→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    56→\n    57→const SHARED_TABLES = `\n    58→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS personas (\n    59→  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n    60→  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n    61→  name TEXT NOT NULL,\n    62→  description TEXT,\n    63→  system_prompt TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n    64→  structured_prompt TEXT,\n    65→  icon TEXT,\n    66→  color TEXT,\n    67→  enabled INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,\n    68→  max_concurrent INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,\n    69→  timeout_ms INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 300000,\n    70→  inference_profile_id TEXT,\n    71→  network_policy TEXT,\n    72→  max_budget_usd REAL,\n    73→  max_turns INTEGER,\n    74→  design_context TEXT,\n    75→  group_id TEXT,\n    76→  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n    77→  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n    78→);\n    79→\n    80→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_tool_definitions (\n    81→  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n    82→  name TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n    83→  category TEXT NOT NULL,\n    84→  description TEXT NOT NULL,\n    85→  script_path TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n    86→  input_schema TEXT,\n    87→  output_schema TEXT,\n    88→  requires_credential_type TEXT,\n    89→  implementation_guide TEXT,\n    90→  is_builtin INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n    91→  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n    92→  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n    93→);\n    94→\n    95→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_tools (\n    96→  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES personas(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    97→  tool_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES persona_tool_definitions(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    98→  PRIMARY KEY (persona_id, tool_id)\n    99→);\n   100→\n   101→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_credentials (\n   102→  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n   103→  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n   104→  name TEXT NOT NULL,\n   105→  service_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n   106→  encrypted_data TEXT NOT NULL,\n   107→  iv TEXT NOT NULL,\n   108→  tag TEXT NOT NULL,\n   109→  metadata TEXT,\n   110→  last_used_at TEXT,\n   111→  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n   112→  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n   113→);\n   114→\n   115→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_credential_links (\n   116→  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES personas(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n   117→  credential_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES persona_credentials(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n   118→  PRIMARY KEY (persona_id, credential_id)\n   119→);\n   120→\n   121→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_events (\n   122→  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n   123→  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n   124→  event_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n   125→  source_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n   126→  source_id TEXT,\n   127→  target_persona_id TEXT,\n   128→  payload TEXT,\n   129→  status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',\n   130→  error_message TEXT,\n   131→  processed_at TEXT,\n   132→  use_case_id TEXT,\n   133→  created_at TEXT NOT NULL\n   134→);\n   135→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pe_status ON persona_events(status);\n   136→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pe_created_status ON persona_events(created_at, status);\n   137→\n   138→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_event_subscriptions (\n   139→  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n   140→  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n   141→  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES personas(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n   142→  event_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n   143→  source_filter TEXT,\n   144→  enabled INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,\n   145→  use_case_id TEXT,\n   146→  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n   147→  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n   148→);\n   149→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pes_event_type ON persona_event_subscriptions(event_type, enabled);\n   150→\n   151→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_triggers (\n   152→  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n   153→  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n   154→  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES personas(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n   155→  trigger_type TEXT NOT NULL CHECK(trigger_type IN ('manual','schedule','polling','webhook','chain')),\n   156→  config TEXT,\n   157→  enabled INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,\n   158→  last_triggered_at TEXT,\n   159→  next_trigger_at TEXT,\n   160→  use_case_id TEXT,\n   161→  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n   162→  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n   163→);\n   164→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pt_due ON persona_triggers(enabled, next_trigger_at);\n   165→\n   166→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_executions (\n   167→  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n   168→  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n   169→  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n   170→  trigger_id TEXT,\n   171→  use_case_id TEXT,\n   172→  status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'queued' CHECK(status IN ('queued','running','completed','failed','cancelled')),\n   173→  input_data TEXT,\n   174→  output_data TEXT,\n   175→  claude_session_id TEXT,\n   176→  model_used TEXT,\n   177→  input_tokens INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n   178→  output_tokens INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n   179→  cost_usd REAL DEFAULT 0,\n   180→  error_message TEXT,\n   181→  duration_ms INTEGER,\n   182→  retry_of_execution_id TEXT,\n   183→  retry_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n   184→  started_at TEXT,\n   185→  completed_at TEXT,\n   186→  created_at TEXT NOT NULL\n   187→);\n   188→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pex_persona ON persona_executions(persona_id);\n   189→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pex_status ON persona_executions(status);\n   190→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pex_created_status ON persona_executions(created_at, status);\n   191→\n   192→${DAILY_METRICS_TABLE}\n   193→\n   194→${INFERENCE_PROFILES_TABLE}\n   195→`;\n   196→\n   197→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   198→// Migrations (legacy single-db)\n   199→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   200→\n   201→function runLegacyMigrations(db: Database.Database, logger: Logger): void {\n   202→  const tablesToMigrate = [\n   203→    'persona_credentials',\n   204→    'persona_event_subscriptions',\n   205→    'persona_triggers',\n   206→    'persona_executions',\n   207→  ];\n   208→\n   209→  for (const table of tablesToMigrate) {\n   210→    const columns = stmt(db,`PRAGMA table_info(${table})`).all() as Array<{ name: string }>;\n   211→    const hasProjectId = columns.some(c => c.name === 'project_id');\n   212→    if (!hasProjectId) {\n   213→      db.exec(`ALTER TABLE ${table} ADD COLUMN project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default'`);\n   214→      logger.info({ table }, 'Migration: added project_id column');\n   215→    }\n   216→  }\n   217→\n   218→  db.exec(`\n   219→    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_personas_project ON personas(project_id);\n   220→    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pe_project ON persona_events(project_id);\n   221→    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pcred_project ON persona_credentials(project_id);\n   222→    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pes_project ON persona_event_subscriptions(project_id);\n   223→    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pes_event_type ON persona_event_subscriptions(event_type, enabled);\n   224→    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pt_project ON persona_triggers(project_id);\n   225→    DROP INDEX IF EXISTS idx_pt_next_trigger;\n   226→    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pt_due ON persona_triggers(enabled, next_trigger_at);\n   227→    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pex_project ON persona_executions(project_id);\n   228→  `);\n   229→\n   230→  // Add inference_profile_id to personas if missing\n   231→  const personaCols = stmt(db,'PRAGMA table_info(personas)').all() as Array<{ name: string }>;\n   232→  if (!personaCols.some(c => c.name === 'inference_profile_id')) {\n   233→    db.exec('ALTER TABLE personas ADD COLUMN inference_profile_id TEXT');\n   234→    logger.info('Migration: added inference_profile_id to personas');\n   235→  }\n   236→  if (!personaCols.some(c => c.name === 'network_policy')) {\n   237→    db.exec('ALTER TABLE personas ADD COLUMN network_policy TEXT');\n   238→    logger.info('Migration: added network_policy to personas');\n   239→  }\n   240→\n   241→  // Create inference_profiles table if missing\n   242→  db.exec(INFERENCE_PROFILES_TABLE);\n   243→}\n   244→\n   245→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   246→// Initialization\n   247→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   248→\n   249→/** Legacy: initialize a single monolithic database (used by migration script). */\n   250→export function initDb(dbPath: string, logger: Logger): Database.Database {\n   251→  const db = new Database(dbPath);\n   252→  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n   253→  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n   254→\n   255→  db.exec(SHARED_TABLES);\n   256→  runLegacyMigrations(db, logger);\n   257→  logger.info({ dbPath }, 'Database initialized (legacy single-db)');\n   258→  return db;\n   259→}\n   260→\n   261→/** Initialize the system-level database (tenant registry). */\n   262→export function initSystemDb(dbPath: string, logger: Logger): Database.Database {\n   263→  const db = new Database(dbPath);\n   264→  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n   265→  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n   266→\n   267→  db.exec(SYSTEM_SCHEMA);\n   268→  logger.info({ dbPath }, 'System database initialized');\n   269→  return db;\n   270→}\n   271→\n   272→/** Initialize a per-tenant database. */\n   273→export function initTenantDb(dbPath: string, logger: Logger): Database.Database {\n   274→  const db = new Database(dbPath);\n   275→  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n   276→  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n   277→\n   278→  db.exec(SHARED_TABLES);\n   279→  logger.info({ dbPath }, 'Tenant database initialized');\n   280→  return db;\n   281→}\n   282→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f1f887ea-5b46-4605-8517-7e434fbc8705","uuid":"4f801d76-8f2d-485f-a432-9e1014af1faf","timestamp":"2026-03-18T11:32:43.529Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\db\\schema.ts","content":"import Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport type { Logger } from 'pino';\nimport { stmt } from './_helpers.js';\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// System schema (tenant registry)\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nconst SYSTEM_SCHEMA = `\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS tenants (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  name TEXT,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\n`;\n\nconst INFERENCE_PROFILES_TABLE = `\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS inference_profiles (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n  name TEXT NOT NULL,\n  provider TEXT NOT NULL,\n  model TEXT,\n  base_url TEXT,\n  auth_token_encrypted TEXT,\n  auth_token_iv TEXT,\n  auth_token_tag TEXT,\n  env_mappings TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]',\n  remove_env_keys TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]',\n  is_preset INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\n`;\n\nconst DAILY_METRICS_TABLE = `\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS daily_metrics (\n  date TEXT NOT NULL,\n  total_executions INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  completed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  failed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  total_cost_usd REAL DEFAULT 0,\n  total_duration_ms INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  PRIMARY KEY (date)\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS retention_watermark (\n  key TEXT PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT 'executions',\n  last_rowid INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0\n);\n`;\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Shared entity tables (used by both legacy single-db and per-tenant dbs)\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nconst SHARED_TABLES = `\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS personas (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n  name TEXT NOT NULL,\n  description TEXT,\n  system_prompt TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n  structured_prompt TEXT,\n  icon TEXT,\n  color TEXT,\n  enabled INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,\n  max_concurrent INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,\n  timeout_ms INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 300000,\n  inference_profile_id TEXT,\n  network_policy TEXT,\n  max_budget_usd REAL,\n  max_turns INTEGER,\n  design_context TEXT,\n  group_id TEXT,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_tool_definitions (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  name TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n  category TEXT NOT NULL,\n  description TEXT NOT NULL,\n  script_path TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n  input_schema TEXT,\n  output_schema TEXT,\n  requires_credential_type TEXT,\n  implementation_guide TEXT,\n  is_builtin INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_tools (\n  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES personas(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n  tool_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES persona_tool_definitions(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n  PRIMARY KEY (persona_id, tool_id)\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_credentials (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n  name TEXT NOT NULL,\n  service_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n  encrypted_data TEXT NOT NULL,\n  iv TEXT NOT NULL,\n  tag TEXT NOT NULL,\n  metadata TEXT,\n  last_used_at TEXT,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_credential_links (\n  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES personas(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n  credential_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES persona_credentials(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n  PRIMARY KEY (persona_id, credential_id)\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_events (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n  event_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n  source_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n  source_id TEXT,\n  target_persona_id TEXT,\n  payload TEXT,\n  status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',\n  error_message TEXT,\n  processed_at TEXT,\n  use_case_id TEXT,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pe_status ON persona_events(status);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pe_created_status ON persona_events(created_at, status);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_event_subscriptions (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES personas(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n  event_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n  source_filter TEXT,\n  enabled INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,\n  use_case_id TEXT,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pes_event_type ON persona_event_subscriptions(event_type, enabled);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_triggers (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES personas(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n  trigger_type TEXT NOT NULL CHECK(trigger_type IN ('manual','schedule','polling','webhook','chain')),\n  config TEXT,\n  enabled INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,\n  last_triggered_at TEXT,\n  next_trigger_at TEXT,\n  use_case_id TEXT,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pt_due ON persona_triggers(enabled, next_trigger_at);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_executions (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  trigger_id TEXT,\n  use_case_id TEXT,\n  status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'queued' CHECK(status IN ('queued','running','completed','failed','cancelled')),\n  input_data TEXT,\n  output_data TEXT,\n  claude_session_id TEXT,\n  model_used TEXT,\n  input_tokens INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  output_tokens INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  cost_usd REAL DEFAULT 0,\n  error_message TEXT,\n  duration_ms INTEGER,\n  retry_of_execution_id TEXT,\n  retry_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  started_at TEXT,\n  completed_at TEXT,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pex_persona ON persona_executions(persona_id);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pex_status ON persona_executions(status);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pex_created_status ON persona_executions(created_at, status);\n\n${DAILY_METRICS_TABLE}\n\n${INFERENCE_PROFILES_TABLE}\n`;\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Migrations (legacy single-db)\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nfunction runLegacyMigrations(db: Database.Database, logger: Logger): void {\n  const tablesToMigrate = [\n    'persona_credentials',\n    'persona_event_subscriptions',\n    'persona_triggers',\n    'persona_executions',\n  ];\n\n  for (const table of tablesToMigrate) {\n    const columns = stmt(db,`PRAGMA table_info(${table})`).all() as Array<{ name: string }>;\n    const hasProjectId = columns.some(c => c.name === 'project_id');\n    if (!hasProjectId) {\n      db.exec(`ALTER TABLE ${table} ADD COLUMN project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default'`);\n      logger.info({ table }, 'Migration: added project_id column');\n    }\n  }\n\n  db.exec(`\n    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_personas_project ON personas(project_id);\n    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pe_project ON persona_events(project_id);\n    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pcred_project ON persona_credentials(project_id);\n    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pes_project ON persona_event_subscriptions(project_id);\n    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pes_event_type ON persona_event_subscriptions(event_type, enabled);\n    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pt_project ON persona_triggers(project_id);\n    DROP INDEX IF EXISTS idx_pt_next_trigger;\n    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pt_due ON persona_triggers(enabled, next_trigger_at);\n    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pex_project ON persona_executions(project_id);\n  `);\n\n  // Add inference_profile_id to personas if missing\n  const personaCols = stmt(db,'PRAGMA table_info(personas)').all() as Array<{ name: string }>;\n  if (!personaCols.some(c => c.name === 'inference_profile_id')) {\n    db.exec('ALTER TABLE personas ADD COLUMN inference_profile_id TEXT');\n    logger.info('Migration: added inference_profile_id to personas');\n  }\n  if (!personaCols.some(c => c.name === 'network_policy')) {\n    db.exec('ALTER TABLE personas ADD COLUMN network_policy TEXT');\n    logger.info('Migration: added network_policy to personas');\n  }\n\n  // Create inference_profiles table if missing\n  db.exec(INFERENCE_PROFILES_TABLE);\n}\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Initialization\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n/** Legacy: initialize a single monolithic database (used by migration script). */\nexport function initDb(dbPath: string, logger: Logger): Database.Database {\n  const db = new Database(dbPath);\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n\n  db.exec(SHARED_TABLES);\n  runLegacyMigrations(db, logger);\n  logger.info({ dbPath }, 'Database initialized (legacy single-db)');\n  return db;\n}\n\n/** Initialize the system-level database (tenant registry). */\nexport function initSystemDb(dbPath: string, logger: Logger): Database.Database {\n  const db = new Database(dbPath);\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n\n  db.exec(SYSTEM_SCHEMA);\n  logger.info({ dbPath }, 'System database initialized');\n  return db;\n}\n\n/** Initialize a per-tenant database. */\nexport function initTenantDb(dbPath: string, logger: Logger): Database.Database {\n  const db = new Database(dbPath);\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n\n  db.exec(SHARED_TABLES);\n  logger.info({ dbPath }, 'Tenant database initialized');\n  return db;\n}\n","numLines":282,"startLine":1,"totalLines":282}}}
[2026-03-18T11:33:07.238Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01L7cXdPYG2cD482bahTXB7Z","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the Event Bus & Subscriptions context. Let me analyze what I've found:\n\n1. **Event Processor** (`eventProcessor.ts`): A 2-second polling loop that:\n   - Fetches pending events in batches of 50\n   - Matches them against subscriptions using `matchEvent()`\n   - Batch-fetches personas, tools, and running counts\n   - Enforces concurrency limits per persona\n   - Dispatches executions after transaction commits\n   - Has stale event recovery at startup and periodic reaping\n\n2. **Bus matching** (`bus.ts`): Simple event matching with:\n   - Target persona filtering\n   - Source filter matching (exact or prefix wildcard)\n   - No complex pattern matching, no content-based routing\n\n3. **Event types** (`types.ts`): Events have type, source, payload, target persona. Subscriptions match on event type + source filter.\n\n4. **HTTP API** (`httpApi.ts`): CRUD for events, subscriptions, webhook ingestion, GitLab webhook support.\n\n5. **DB layer** (`events.ts`): Standard CRUD with pending event polling, status updates, stale event recovery.\n\nThe system is fundamentally a simple polling-based event bus with 2-second intervals and straightforward matching logic—no complex pattern matching or content-based routing involved.\n\nLooking at what's missing, there's no CEP capabilities, event chaining, conditional logic, replay/sourcing, schema validation, real-time streaming, or event transformation pipelines. Processing is single-threaded per tenant with no persona orchestration support.\n\nI'm thinking about moonshot ideas to unlock the system's potential. One direction is adding a Complex Event Processing engine that detects patterns across streams—like triggering a persona when event A is followed by event B within a time window. Another is building a DAG-based workflow engine that lets personas compose into declarative orchestrations.\n\nI could also explore predictive pre-warming using historical patterns to anticipate which personas will be needed, or implement full event sourcing with replay capabilities for debugging and what-if analysis. A semantic routing layer using embeddings would replace the primitive exact/wildcard filtering with natural language event matching.\n\nNow I'm documenting these ideas and saving them for further exploration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6930,"cache_read_input_tokens":40956,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6930},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f1f887ea-5b46-4605-8517-7e434fbc8705","uuid":"b4cfa546-6e5a-410a-992e-622f3961c348"}
